  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research contexts involving Class III ventricular assist devices. The CFD hemolysis prediction workflow for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump was assessed under Model Risk Level 5 conditions. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all 13 credibility factors; seven factors were formally assessed and six were flagged as epistemic gaps. The assessment team concluded that the achieved credibility levels, while below required thresholds in several dimensions, are sufficient for the stated low-risk advisory use. No structured Context of Use record is attached to this package; intended-use scope is described only in the narrative above.",
